<br>
It all begins with the challenges, you challenge a person or a bunch of people to do an fc match with and they have to draw a character and so do you. Then if all goes well you begin a new thread in the matches section to do the fight club thing you challenged or accepted in the challenges section... do you follow?<br>
<br>
Ok so let's say your challenge in the challenges section was named: &quot;Super Cool Melee Fight!&quot; then if a person or people accept it then when youre given the go ahead signal when everyone has posted there characters u begin a new thread in the matches area called like &quot;Super Melee Fight MATCH&quot; or something to that extent so people know which match corresponds to which challenge, got it?<br>
<br>
Now let's talk about how this fight club thing is DONE! Fight club matches go in sequentials, most people over here like to draw comic pages for sequentials, that is the easiest and most common form of fight club and the only type you will probably see nowadays. So you decide on the order of who will go first to last to draw and then you begin!<br>
<br>
